org.azyva.dragom.job

Class Build

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.azyva.dragom.job.RootModuleVersionJobAbstractImpl
      • org.azyva.dragom.job.Build

  • public class Build
extends RootModuleVersionJobAbstractImpl
    Build job.

    The reference graph is traversed depth first and the BuilderPlugin is used to build each ModuleVersion sequentially.

    Currently, parallelism is not supported.

    Author:
    David Raymond

    • Field Detail

      • RUNTIME_PROPERTY_BUILD_SCOPE

        public static final String RUNTIME_PROPERTY_BUILD_SCOPE
        Runtime property that specifies the BuildScope. The default value is BuildScope#ONLY_USER if not defined.

        A runtime property is used so that it is possible to set a default in a context that is more global than the tool invocation. But often this runtime property will be provided by the user as a tool initialization property for each tool invocation.

        It is accessed in the context of each Module so that its value can be different for each Module. But in general it will be defined for the root NodePath only.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
